title.narrative: Feed the Future Tajikistan Agriculture and Water Activity (TAWA)

description.narrative: (Tajikistan): .The FTF Tajikistan Agriculture and Water Activity (TAWA) will improve the nutrition of women of childbearing age and children under two by increasing the production and consumption of crops and livestock products high in vitamin A, iron, zinc, and animal proteins to address stunting and wasting in the Khatlon Province. With FY 2018 funds, TAWA will continue to introduce and build on previous interventions through technology transfer and promotion of good agricultural practices to support the growth and sustainable development of the agriculture extension, vegetable, fruit, dairy, and irrigation sectors. Through TAWA, local extension providers will support the establishment of women's groups and facilitate training and demonstrations on multiple agriculture themes. TAWA will introduce a voucher program to scale-up and promote the production, consumption, and sales of nutritious crops and provide technical assistance to private sector owned greenhouses growing improved varieties of tomato, sweet pepper, and cucumber seedlings. In addition, the activity will support peach tree production with improved practices on demonstration farms to teach smallholder farmers proper maintenance of orchards and nurseries. Finally, TAWA will support the dairy sector through increased production and quality of milk by administering a voucher programs enabling livestock farmers to scale up the production of dairy cattle forage crops and/or adopt new efficient and labor-saving technologies, such as planters, mowers and balers. Together these interventions will increase incomes of smallholder farmers and improve the health of women and children in at-risk communities increasing resilience to shocks which will in turn support Tajikistan on the road to self-reliance and strengthen its sovereignty and independence. This program will contribute to the Joint Strategic Plan Mission Objective 3.1: Promote Tajikistan's competitiveness in regional and international markets..
